The minimum wage for employees in the farm and forestry sector will increase by 5.6%. The Labour Department made the announcement on Tuesday. Department spokesperson Teboho Thejane said the new minimum wage would come into effect on 1 March until 28 February 2019. The wages will increase as follows: Monthly: R3 001,13 to R3 169,19
Weekly: R692,62 to R731,41
Daily: R138,52 to R146,28
Hourly: R15,39 to R16,25 “The wages are for employees who are working nine hours a day,” Thejane said. -TNA Reporter